Compute $\dbinom{1293}{1}$.
inference:
Using the definition of binomial coefficients, we have
$$\binom{n}{k} = \frac{n!}{k!(n-k)!}$$
In this case, $n=1293$ and $k=1$. Therefore,
$$\binom{1293}{1} = \frac{1293!}{1!(1293-1)!} = \frac{1293!}{1!1292!} = \frac{1293 \times 1292!}{1 \times 1292!} = 1293.$$
Final Answer: $\boxed{1293}$
